            {
                id = "before", speaker = "Sable, of Hollowmere",
                text = "*(A small, fierce light comes up in her.)* Hollowmere had a millpond the color of weak tea, and an apple tree older than the village that everyone swore was haunted and no one would cut down, and a festival in autumn where we floated candles for the year's dead so they'd not be forgotten. *(Her voice cracks, then steadies.)* We floated candles *for the dead*, Returned. A whole village's worth of people who believed, with everything they had, that the dead should be *remembered* — and the church walled their wells' poison-source as Faithless, and burned the rest of us to stop the spread. *(quietly)* Tell me how that's the order of a god who keeps the dead. Tell me, because I floated a candle for my husband last autumn and I no longer know which side of the Wall he's on.",
